      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "NOCTILUCENT (2) was out of the placings last time but shapes well for this on her superb win the start prior, getting around Shepparton over 390m in 21.96. Has the ability and expected to go close again. PERIODICAL (7) hit the ground running from the squeeze draw with a slick early split, holding on for a minor placing when second and beaten a neck at Warragul over 400m in 22.78. Nicely placed to grab a well-deserved win. BULL DURHAM (6) was in the minors two back (22.17) at Warrnambool but ran below best last time at Warragul, finishing 6th. Form here at the trip sound including two wins. Will give the top chances plenty to think about. SARSAPARILLA KID (3) was in the money last start at big odds - poses a threat again.",
